{"title_page": "Roald Amundsen (railcar)", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{External links|date=March 2020}}\n{{No footnotes|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox train\n| background       = darkgreen\n| name             = ''Roald Amundsen'' Pullman car\n| image            = SD-Roald Amundsen Pullman Private Railroad Car 1928.jpg\n| imagesize        = \n| imagealt         = \n| caption          = The ''Roald Amundsen'' on display in Scottsdale, Arizona\n| interiorimage    = \n| interiorimagealt = \n| interiorcaption  = \n| service          = \n| manufacturer     = [[Pullman Company]]\n| ordernumber      = Lot 6246\n| factory          = \n| family           = \n| replaced         = \n| yearconstruction = 1929\n| yearservice      = \n| refurbishment    = \n| yearscrapped     = \n| numberconstruction= \n| numberbuilt      = \n| numberservice    = \n| numberpreserved  = \n| numberscrapped   = \n| formation        = \n| diagram          = Pullman Plan 3972C\n| code             = \n| fleetnumbers     = \n| capacity         = \n| operator         = \n| depots           = \n| lines            =\n\n| carbody          = \n| carlength        = \n| width            = \n| height           = \n| floorheight      = \n| platformheight   = \n| entrylevelorstep = \n| doors            = \n| art-sections     = \n| wheeldiameter    = \n| wheelbase        = \n| maxspeed         = \n| weight           =\n| axleload         = \n| aux              = \n| powersupply      = \n| hvac             = \n| bogies           = \n| brakes           = \n| coupling         = \n| gauge            = {{RailGauge|ussg}}\n{{Infobox NRHP\n | embed = yes\n | name = Roald Amundsen Pullman Private Railroad Car\n | nrhp_type = \n | image = \n | caption = \n | location = [[Maricopa County, Arizona]], [[United States|USA]]\n | nearest_city = [[Scottsdale, Arizona]]\n | coordinates = {{coord|33|32|15|N|111|55|22|W|display=inline,title}}\n| area = \n | designated_nrhp_type = August 6, 2009\n | added = \n | visitation_num = \n | visitation_year = \n | governing_body = \n | architect = \n | architecture = \n | refnum = 09000582<ref name=\"nris\">{{NRISref|version=2013a|dateform=mdy|accessdate=2020-04-03|refnum=09000582|name=Roald Amundsen Pullman Private Railroad Car}}</ref>\n}}}}\n\n\nNamed after the [[Roald Amundsen|Norwegian explorer]], the '''''Roald Amundsen''''' is a former [[Pullman Company]] [[private railroad car|private car]]; the last of seven Explorer-series cars built between 1927 and 1929 for the Pullman Company's pool of passenger cars. It was frequently used as the United States [[Transportation of the President of the United States#Presidential%20railcars|Presidential Rail Car]], and was used for every president from Herbert Hoover through Dwight Eisenhower.{{sfn|Wrixon|2008|p=26}}\n\nDuring World War II, sister car ''[[Ferdinand Magellan (railcar)|Ferdinand Magellan]]'' was rebuilt as the official presidential private car; after the war, the ''Roald Amundsen'' was surplus to the Pullman Company's requirements and was sold, and became a [[business car]] for the [[New York Central Railroad]]. In 1971 it was donated to the [[McCormick-Stillman Railroad Park]] in Scottsdale, Arizona.<ref name=\"nris\" />\n\nIn 2009 the ''Roald Amundsen'' was placed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]].\n\n== References ==<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n<references group=\"\" responsive=\"1\"></references>'''Bibliography'''\n* Klara, Robert (2010). FDR'S Funeral Train {{ISBN|780230108035}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Wrixon |first=Fred B. |year=2008 |title=FDR's wartime train travels |journal=Classic Trains Special Edition No. 6: Railroads and World War II |issn=1541-809X |pages=20\u201330 |ref=harv}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.scottsdaleaz.gov/Assets/ScottsdaleAZ/Historic+Preservation/SHRrpt+Roald+Amundsen+Pullmen+Car+Report.pdf Historic Significance and Integrity Assessment Report for the Roald Amundsen Pullman Car]\n* [https://www.therailroadpark.com/rides-and-attractions/exhibits/ Scottsdale Railroad Museum]\n* [http://www.thehistoryreader.com/contemporary-history/fdrs-funeral-train/ FDR Funeral Train]\n\n\n[[Category:Rail passenger cars of the United States]]\n{{US-train-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{External links|date=March 2020}}\n{{No footnotes|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox train\n| background       = darkgreen\n| name             = ''Roald Amundsen'' Pullman car\n| image            = SD-Roald Amundsen Pullman Private Railroad Car 1928.jpg\n| imagesize        = \n| imagealt         = \n| caption          = The ''Roald Amundsen'' on display in Scottsdale, Arizona\n| interiorimage    = \n| interiorimagealt = \n| interiorcaption  = \n| service          = \n| manufacturer     = [[Pullman Company]]\n| ordernumber      = Lot 6246\n| factory          = \n| family           = \n| replaced         = \n| yearconstruction = 1929\n| yearservice      = \n| refurbishment    = \n| yearscrapped     = \n| numberconstruction= \n| numberbuilt      = \n| numberservice    = \n| numberpreserved  = \n| numberscrapped   = \n| formation        = \n| diagram          = Pullman Plan 3972C\n| code             = \n| fleetnumbers     = \n| capacity         = \n| operator         = \n| depots           = \n| lines            =\n\n| carbody          = \n| carlength        = \n| width            = \n| height           = \n| floorheight      = \n| platformheight   = \n| entrylevelorstep = \n| doors            = \n| art-sections     = \n| wheeldiameter    = \n| wheelbase        = \n| maxspeed         = \n| weight           =\n| axleload         = \n| aux              = \n| powersupply      = \n| hvac             = \n| bogies           = \n| brakes           = \n| coupling         = \n| gauge            = {{RailGauge|ussg}}\n{{Infobox NRHP\n | embed = yes\n | name = Roald Amundsen Pullman Private Railroad Car\n | nrhp_type = \n | image = \n | caption = \n | location = [[Maricopa County, Arizona]], [[United States|USA]]\n | nearest_city = [[Scottsdale, Arizona]]\n | coordinates = {{coord|33|32|15|N|111|55|22|W|display=inline,title}}\n| area = \n | designated_nrhp_type = August 6, 2009\n | added = \n | visitation_num = \n | visitation_year = \n | governing_body = \n | architect = \n | architecture = \n | refnum = 09000582<ref name=\"nris\">{{NRISref|version=2013a|dateform=mdy|accessdate=2020-04-03|refnum=09000582|name=Roald Amundsen Pullman Private Railroad Car}}</ref>\n}}}}\n\n\nNamed after the [[Roald Amundsen|Norwegian explorer]], the '''''Roald Amundsen''''' is a former [[Pullman Company]] [[private railroad car|private car]]; the last of seven Explorer-series cars built between 1927 and 1929 for the Pullman Company's pool of passenger cars. It was frequently used as the United States [[Transportation of the President of the United States#Presidential%20railcars|Presidential Rail Car]], and was used for every president from Herbert Hoover through Dwight Eisenhower.{{sfn|Wrixon|2008|p=26}}\n\nDuring World War II, sister car ''[[Ferdinand Magellan (railcar)|Ferdinand Magellan]]'' was rebuilt as the official presidential private car; after the war, the ''Roald Amundsen'' was surplus to the Pullman Company's requirements and was sold, and became a [[business car]] for the [[New York Central Railroad]]. In 1971 it was donated to the [[McCormick-Stillman Railroad Park]] in Scottsdale, Arizona.<ref name=\"nris\" />\n\nIn 2009 the ''Roald Amundsen'' was placed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]].\n\n== References ==<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n<references group=\"\" responsive=\"1\"></references>'''Bibliography'''\n* Klara, Robert (2010). FDR'S Funeral Train [[International Standard Book Number|ISBN]] [[Special:BookSources/780230108035|780230108035]]\n* {{cite journal |last=Wrixon |first=Fred B. |year=2008 |title=FDR's wartime train travels |journal=Classic Trains Special Edition No. 6: Railroads and World War II |issn=1541-809X |pages=20\u201330 |ref=harv}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.scottsdaleaz.gov/Assets/ScottsdaleAZ/Historic+Preservation/SHRrpt+Roald+Amundsen+Pullmen+Car+Report.pdf Historic Significance and Integrity Assessment Report for the Roald Amundsen Pullman Car]\n* [https://www.therailroadpark.com/rides-and-attractions/exhibits/ Scottsdale Railroad Museum]\n* [http://www.thehistoryreader.com/contemporary-history/fdrs-funeral-train/ FDR Funeral Train]\n\n\n[[Category:Rail passenger cars of the United States]]\n{{US-train-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Jonesey95", "label": "safe", "comment": "FixISBN erroror other ISBN error usingAutoEd(or wrap invalid ISBN in template to show error message)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roald_Amundsen_(railcar)"}
